      <description>Biography Trey Batey is an instructor of social sciences at Lower Columbia College in Longview, Washington. He is a broadly-trained anthropologist with experience focused in human skeletal biology, as applied to the fields of bioarchaeology and forensic anthropology.
Personally, he occasionally plays the drums, enjoys spending time outdoors with his family, and is a rabid fan of LSU athletics.</description>
